{
  "texts": [
    "Limited access to training data and processes prevents confidence over bias.",
    "A model's outputs reflect the data they are trained upon; therefore, without clarity of training processes and data, the extent and ways in which GPT-4 contains encoded biases and interests of third-party data sources is unclear.",
    "More confidence and uncertainty estimation are needed, particularly in high-risk settings.",
    "GPT-4 will perform differently on different tasks and spheres of knowledge based on the information it is trained on.",
    "However, without providing users with an estimation of confidence, each response will be taken with the same, despite different performances."
  ]
}